attributeList.attribute: An ATP-dependent chromatin remodelling complex which disrupts the nucleosome structure, increases the binding of transcription factors to nucleosomes, mobilizes histone octamers along DNA in cis, transfers histone octamers to different DNA fragments, displaces histone H2A/H2B dimers and generates superhelical torsion in DNA. Binds preferentially to four-way DNA and promotes resection initiation at a DNA double-strand break. Binds to DNA and nucleosomes without any DNA sequence specificity.

Molecular weight = 1.14MDa. Assembles around a catalytic subunit that contains a central ATPase domain and flanking sequences that recruit auxiliary subunits. The auxiliary subunits SNF5 and SWI3 ensure nucleosome occupancy at promoters and targeting to histones. RTT102 acts as a stabilizing factor for the Arp7/9 heterodimer, enhancing its interaction with nucleotide.
